CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 6, 1957, pg. 18 reads: "4. The Restland-Lincoln Memorial Parks booth with representatives, left to right, Darwin Taylor, salesman; Thomas Logan and Ted Tamplin, division manager, and Mrs. Dolores Redwood, who added life to the booth."
TitMainTitle: Darwin Taylor, Dolores Redwood, Thomas Logan, and Ted Tamplin, standing in Restland-Lincoln Memorial Parks booth in Syria Mosque for the 1957 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
